


     FFFFOOOORRRRCCCCEEEEHHHHIIII((((UUUU1111))))          LLLLSSSS----DDDDOOOOSSSS 6666 ---- UUUUttttiiiilllliiiittttiiiieeeessss 1111           FFFFOOOORRRRCCCCEEEEHHHHIIII((((UUUU1111))))



     NNNNaaaammmmeeee
          FORCEHI - Reserves low memory so that drivers or filters can
          be forced into high memory.

     SSSSyyyynnnnttttaaaaxxxx
          ffffoooorrrrcccceeeehhhhiiii [ ----qqqqrrrrffff????hhhh ] [ ; _n_e_x_t _c_o_m_m_a_n_d ]

     DDDDeeeessssccccrrrriiiippppttttiiiioooonnnn
          _F_o_r_c_e_h_i allows the user to lock low memory so that any
          drivers or filters that are subsequently loaded will be
          forced to use high memory instead of low memory.  Since low
          memory is a limited resource and some drivers can only be
          loaded into low memory, _f_o_r_c_e_h_i can be used to force drivers
          and filters that can be run in high memory to use high
          memory, leaving low memory available for the drivers that
          require it.

          _F_o_r_c_e_h_i accepts several options.  Options are specified by
          single characters, and they may be entered in upper or
          lowercase.  Options are always preceded by a hyphen (a "-").
          If you are specifying multiple options, you can specify the
          options in any of these formats:
                -a -b -c   or   -abc   or   -a -bc   or  -ab -c

          The options are:

          ----qqqq   This option causes _f_o_r_c_e_h_i to run silently.  No
               messages are displayed if everything works like it
               should.  If errors occur, they are reported.

          ----rrrr   By default, _f_o_r_c_e_h_i will reserve low memory so that no
               other drivers can be loaded there.  The ----rrrr option
               releases any memory that was reserved by _f_o_r_c_e_h_i.

          ----ffff   Similar to the ----qqqq, except that _f_o_r_c_e_h_i will not display
               any messages, even if the requested action fails.

          ----???? oooorrrr ----hhhh
               Displays the help message.

          ; _n_e_x_t _c_o_m_m_a_n_d
               After _f_o_r_c_e_h_i completes, the remainder of the command
               line is executed as a second command.  The command
               ffffoooorrrrcccceeeehhhhiiii;;;;sssseeeetttt ****ccccllll ccccoooommmm will reserve all of low memory, and
               then the RS-232 driver will be loaded.










