     FFFFOOOORRRRCCCCEEEEHHHHIIII((((UUUU1111))))          LLLLSSSS----DDDDOOOOSSSS 6666 ---- UUUUttttiiiilllliiiittttiiiieeeessss 1111           FFFFOOOORRRRCCCCEEEEHHHHIIII((((UUUU1111))))



     NNNNooootttteeeessss
          _F_o_r_c_e_h_i will not cause a driver that can only run in low
          memory to be usable in high memory.

          The _s_y_s_g_e_n(_L) command should not be used while _f_o_r_c_e_h_i has
          memory reserved.  You can determine if _f_o_r_c_e_h_i is holding
          memory by using the _m_a_p_m_e_m(U1) command to examine the
          contents of memory.

     FFFFiiiilllleeeessss
          No files are accessed by _f_o_r_c_e_h_i.


          If you need more information on _f_o_r_c_e_h_i(U1), please write to
